            <!--span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    I have little memory of anything that took place in my life during the years that my family lived on Whittier Street. I imagine that because of my placement in the order of the family, being the youngest of ten living siblings and being a new baby arriving, that I was the recipient of lots of attention. Of course there are the suggestions that I was certainly spoiled and pampered because of this. I do know that I had loving parents and brothers and sisters who cared for my every need and that my years as a small child were filled with loving attention and freedom to play without fear. We lived in that location for approximately four years after I arrived.
            </span>
            
