                Then when Marlon came home from his mission, I believe we picked him up in Salt Lake. When Robert finished his mission in Australia, we planned to make a major trip down to pick him up. Kenneth and I, and Marlon and Debra left to go down to Australia to pick up Robert. We had a trip that lasted six weeks, and we visited many, many countries in the South Pacific. We visited Mike’s mission and met some of the people that he had worked with in New Zealand. We met many of Robert’s friends and had a very special time there with him. Robert served as an assistant to the president, so he had many things that he could show us in Australia. We thoroughly enjoyed that and met his mission president. 
