                    It was kind of interesting how that trip came together, because some of our children just didn’t have the finances to do that trip. They were concerned about it. We wanted to do a family trip for a 50th wedding anniversary, but we didn’t know where we wanted to go or what to do or how long to stay. Finally, Dani called and she said, “Bob is going to put a trip together for us. Let’s go to the Mediterranean. Let’s go take a trip to the Greek Islands.” Oh, my goodness, I thought that would be wonderful. Debra thought it would be wonderful. Bob thought this was wonderful. We began to plan the trip, and pretty soon those who thought they would not go came together, and as a family, all six of our children and their spouses and Ken and I, we made the trip to the Mediterranean.  <br /><br />

                    We went to Rome. We were in Italy for a week or so. We went to the Greek Islands and absolutely fell in love with them. I’ve always wanted to go back to Sorrento in Italy. That was a very special place for me. That was a marvelous trip. The time we spent together as family—we were unbelievably close, helping each other and enjoying the time that we had there. We had some really fun experiences that I would be happy to share with anyone. Anytime they want to listen to me, I’ll tell them of our experiences on that trip.  <br /><br />

